Package arlut.csd.JDataComponent

Interface Summary
JchoiceInterface This interface is used to allow a callback to be done from the ChoiceList to set the component which is attached to that JchoiceList.
JsetValueCallback Client-side interface used to allow callback to be done from GUI components in the arlut.csd.JDataComponent package to the container which contains them.
 

Class Summary
JAddValueObject Subclass of JValueObject that represents the addition of a specific value to a list, or selection in JstringListBox or StringSelector.
JAddVectorValueObject Subclass of JValueObject that represents the addition of a vector to a list.
JButtonPanel This panel contains a row of buttons, with controllable justification within the panel.
JcalendarField This class defines a date input field object, suitable for use in a StringDialog class.
JcheckboxField Subclass of JCheckBox used to connect a checkbox to the standard JsetValueCallback callback.
JchoiceList JchoiceList This class is basically a java.awt.List object with some added functionality.
JcomponentAttr  
JdateField This class defines a Date/Time GUI component that ties into the JsetValueCallback that the Ganymede clients use internally.
JDeleteValueObject Subclass of JValueObject that represents the deletion of an item item in a JstringListBox or the like.
JDeleteVectorValueObject Subclass of JValueObject that represents the deletion of a vector from a list.
JentryDocument Helper class for JentryField and its subclasses.
JentryField JentryField serves as an abstract base class for all GUI fields in the client that use textfields.
JErrorValueObject Subclass of JValueObject that represents an error condition
JFieldWrapper  
JfloatField This class defines a GUI field component that is capable of handling Java doubles.
JFocusRootPanel  
JInsertValueObject Subclass of JValueObject that represents the double clicking of an item in a JstringListBox or StringSelector.
JIPField This class is an IPv4/IPv6 data display/entry widget for Ganymede.
JLabelPanel This panel contains labeled GUI components in a vertical stack orientation.
JMoveValueObject Subclass of JValueObject that represents the movement of a value in a list.
JMultiLineLabel A simple word-wrapping multiline label.
JnumberField This class defines an entry field that is capable of handling integers.
JPanelCombo  
JParameterValueObject Subclass of JValueObject that represents the movement of a value in a list.
JpassField JpassField is the composite two-field GUI component used for entering passwords in the Ganymede client.
JpasswordField This class defines an entry field that is capable of handling strings.
JResetDateObject Subclass of JValueObject that represents a calendar reset operation
JSetValueObject Subclass of JValueObject that represents a simple value set operation
JSpacer This class defines an invisible space holder that can be placed into a GridBagLayout-managed container to make sure that a certain minimum row or column size is maintained.
JStretchPanel This class defines a JPanel that contains a single, centered, stretched component.
JstringArea This is a multi-line, scrollable text component with support for the JsetValueCallback listener interface used for the arlut.csd.JDataComponent graphical components.
JstringField This class defines an entry field that is capable of handling strings.
JstringListBox A sorted listbox that handles listHandle's.
Jtaskbar  
JValueObject A client-side message object used to pass status updates from GUI components in the arlut.csd.JDataComponent package to their containers.
LAFMenu This class is a simple menu which can be added to a Swing app to show (and switch between) a list of installed Swing look and feel themes.
listHandle A wrapper to hold both a String and (optionally) a related object, such as an Invid.
myTextArea This is a custom subclass of JTextArea that provides the inner gui component substrate for the optionally scrollable JstringArea.
StringSelector A two-paneled GUI component for adding or removing strings and/or labeled objects from a list, with an optional list of available strings and/or objects to choose from.
TimedKeySelectionManager A JComboBox KeySelectionManager subclass that can be attached to a JComboBox to allow typing multiple characters of an item name to find it within the JComboBox's model.
